---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does roof restoration cost in Toowoomba?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A full tile roof restoration — high-pressure clean, re-bed and flexible-repoint the ridge capping, replace broken tiles, prime, then two membrane coats — generally costs $4,500–$9,000 for a single-storey Toowoomba home in 2026, with most landing around $6,500–$9,000 for a 150–200m² roof. Pricing by the square metre runs roughly $28–$45/m² for tile and a little more for Colorbond restoration; terracotta costs more than concrete tile because it needs specialised handling. We quote the whole job, not a per-metre rate that leaves out the repairs." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is a restoration worth it, or should I just replace the roof?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "If the tiles themselves are structurally sound and it's the bedding, pointing, coating and a few broken tiles that have aged, a restoration is excellent value — it can add 10–15 years for a fraction of a reroof's cost. If the tiles are delaminating and porous, the battens are rotten, or you've had repeated leaks across the roof, restoration is lipstick on a failing roof and a replacement is the smarter spend. We assess honestly and tell you which one your roof genuinely needs." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is flexible repointing and why does it matter in Toowoomba?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Repointing is renewing the mortar-line that holds your ridge and hip capping in place. Old rigid sand-cement pointing cracks — especially in Toowoomba, where reactive black-soil clays make buildings move seasonally — and once it cracks, water gets in and caps can lift in a storm. Flexible pointing is a modern compound that flexes with that movement instead of cracking off, so the capping stays sealed and secure far longer. We use flexible pointing on every re-bed and restoration." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does a roof restoration take and how long does it last?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A typical single-storey restoration takes 2–4 days, weather permitting — clean and repairs first, then bedding and pointing, then prime and coats with drying time between. A properly done restoration on a sound tile roof generally lasts 10–15 years before it needs recoating, and the re-bedding and repointing last longer again. It's the most cost-effective way to get years more life out of a roof that's tired but not finished." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Roof Restoration Toowoomba | Clean, Re-bed, Repoint, Coat"
  description="Roof restoration in Toowoomba — high-pressure clean, re-bed & flexible-repoint ridge capping, prime & membrane coat to add years to a sound tile roof. QBCC-licensed. ~$4.5K–$9K. Free quote."
  canonical="https://toowoombaroofrepairs.com.au/services/roof-restoration/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Clean &middot; re-bed &middot; flexible repoint &middot; coat</span>
      <h1>Roof restoration across <span class="accent">Toowoomba</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        If your tile roof is tired but not finished &mdash; faded, mossy, with
        cracked pointing and a few broken tiles &mdash; a restoration adds years
        for a fraction of a reroof. High-pressure clean, re-bed and
        flexible-repoint the ridge lines, replace broken tiles, prime and membrane
        coat. ~$4.5K&ndash;$9K for a single storey. QBCC-licensed. Honest advice on
        restore versus replace.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>What a roof restoration involves.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">

        <h3>1. Inspect &amp; the honest call.</h3>
        <p>
          Before we quote a restoration we get on the roof and check the tiles
          themselves are sound. Restoration is brilliant value on a roof
          that&rsquo;s aged on the surface but structurally fine. It&rsquo;s a
          waste of money on one that&rsquo;s genuinely failed &mdash; delaminating,
          porous tiles or rotten battens need a
          <a href="/services/roof-replacement/">reroof</a>, not a coat of paint.
          We tell you which one you&rsquo;ve got, with photos.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">2. High-pressure clean.</h3>
        <p>
          We strip off years of moss, lichen, dirt and chalked-out old coating
          with a high-pressure clean. This is what lets the new coating actually
          bond &mdash; coating over a dirty roof is the classic corner-cut that
          peels within a year or two. The clean also reveals every cracked tile
          and failed pointing line that needs attention.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">3. Repairs &amp; broken-tile replacement.</h3>
        <p>
          We replace cracked and broken tiles (matching profile and colour as
          closely as stock allows) and sort any slipped tiles, flashings and
          valley issues before coating &mdash; see our
          <a href="/services/roof-repairs/">roof repairs</a> page for the detail.
          There&rsquo;s no sense sealing a coat over a roof that&rsquo;s still
          letting water in underneath.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">4. Re-bed &amp; flexible repoint.</h3>
        <p>
          The ridge and hip capping gets re-bedded where the mortar has failed
          and repointed with a <strong>flexible pointing compound</strong>. This
          matters more in Toowoomba than almost anywhere: our reactive black-soil
          clays make buildings move with the seasons, and rigid sand-cement
          pointing simply cracks under that movement. Flexible pointing flexes
          with the roof, so the capping stays sealed and won&rsquo;t lift in the
          next storm.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">5. Prime &amp; membrane coat.</h3>
        <p>
          We seal the cleaned tiles with a primer, then apply two coats of a
          tile-roof membrane in your chosen colour. The result restores the look,
          re-waterproofs the tile surface, and reflects heat &mdash; a real plus
          through a Toowoomba summer. A properly done restoration generally lasts
          10&ndash;15 years before it needs recoating.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Standards, licensing &amp; cost.</h3>
        <p>
          Restoration work over $3,300 must be done by a <strong>QBCC</strong>-licensed
          contractor (check the number on the public register), tiled-roof work
          follows <strong>AS 2050</strong>, any metal detailing follows
          <strong>AS 1562.1</strong>, and fixings are wind-rated to
          <strong>AS 1170.2</strong>. We work at height under WorkSafe
          fall-protection rules. Expect roughly $4,500&ndash;$9,000 for a
          single-storey home, around $28&ndash;$45/m&sup2; &mdash; terracotta
          costs more than concrete tile because it needs specialised handling.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Why we don&rsquo;t cut corners.</h3>
        <p>
          A cheap restoration is the easiest job in roofing to fake: skip the
          proper clean, coat straight over moss and broken tiles, point with rigid
          mortar, and it looks great on handover day. Then it peels, the pointing
          cracks, and the leaks come back. We clean to bare tile, repair first,
          use flexible pointing, and prime before we coat &mdash; so the roof is
          genuinely restored, not just repainted for the photos.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/rangeville/">Rangeville</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/centenary-heights/">Centenary Heights</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/highfields/">Highfields</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/wilsonton/">Wilsonton</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/glenvale/">Glenvale</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/toowoomba-region/">All Toowoomba Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Is your tile roof tired but sound?</h2>
        <p>We&rsquo;ll get up there, tell you honestly whether to restore or replace, and quote a proper restoration &mdash; clean, repair, repoint, coat.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
